Melt chips with sweetened condensed milk, 2 tablespoons, butter, vanilla and salt in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts. Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8- or 9-inch square pan. In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt marshmallows with remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Spread on top of fudge. With table knife or metal spatula, swirl through top of fudge. Chill at least 2 hours or until firm. Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off wax paper and cut into squares. Store covered in refrigerator.